# 詞: 睇怕

1. 呢場波賽好激烈，我哋隊睇怕會輸。 (This football match is very intense; our team is likely to lose.)
2. 佢今日遲咗半個鐘，老闆睇怕會發脾氣。 (He is half an hour late today; the boss is likely to lose his temper.)
3. 天氣預報話有暴雨，郊遊活動睇怕要取消。 (The weather forecast says there will be heavy rain; the picnic activity is likely to be cancelled.)
4. 你成日唔做功課，老師睇怕會找你問話。 (You never do your homework; the teacher is likely to call you in for a chat.)
5. 呢間餐廳太貴，我哋睇怕食唔起。 (This restaurant is too expensive; we are likely to find it unaffordable.)
6. 佢最近壓力好大，睇怕會病倒。 (He has been under a lot of pressure recently; he is likely to fall ill.)
7. 交通好塞車，我哋睇怕會遲到開會。 (Traffic is very congested; we are likely to be late for the meeting.)
8. 部車舊咗，維修費好貴，我哋睇怕要換新車。 (The car is old and repair costs are high; we are likely to need to buy a new car.)
9. 佢講嘢咁大聲，鄰居睇怕會投訴。 (He speaks so loudly; the neighbors are likely to complain.)
10. 呢套戲口碑唔好，票房睇怕會慘淡。 (This movie has poor reviews; its box office performance is likely to be dismal.) [end of text]


